The paper discusses the KG Usage framework, which introduces features to support trust, privacy, and transparency concerns regarding the use of knowledge graphs by applications. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as knowledge graphs are often used in AI applications, databases (cs.DB) as knowledge graphs are a type of database, cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) as the paper specifically addresses privacy concerns, machine learning (cs.LG) as knowledge graphs are often used in machine learning applications, and software engineering (cs.SE) as the framework presented in the paper can be used to develop software applications.
